e-sin-operador-el-centro-de-convenciones&catid=135:actualidad-del-sur&Itemid=423 ''Sin operador el Centro de Convenciones.''] Por Jason Rodríguez Grafal. La Perla del Sur. Ponce, Puerto Rico. 12 October 2012. Retrieved 13 October 2012.</ref> | former_names = Centro de Convenciones de Ponce | banquets = 3,000 | classroom_cap = 3,000 | meeting_cap = 3,000 | theatre = 3,000 | total_space = {{convert|120000|sqft|m2}} | exhibit = {{convert|120000|sqft|m2}} | breakout = 16 | ballroom = 1-16 (convertible) | website = {{URL|http://www.complejoferialpr.com/}} }} {{Sidebar Tourism in Puerto Rico}} '''Complejo Ferial de Puerto Rico''',<ref>[http://www.periodicolaperla.com/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=5351:se-congregaran-en-ponce-disenadores-de-latinoamerica&catid=81:locales&Itemid=198 ''Celebrarán en Ponce feria de diseñadores.''] Reinaldo Millán. La Perla del Sur. Ponce, Puerto Rico. Year 31. Issue 1550. Page 12. 14 August 2013. Retrieved 14 August 2013.</ref> a.k.a. '''Centro de Convenciones de Ponce''', '''Centro de Convenciones de Ponce Juan H. Cintrón''',<ref>[http://www.periodicolaperla.com/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=4363:sigue-sin-operador-el-centro-de-convenciones&catid=135:actualidad-del-sur&Itemid=423 ''Sin operador el Centro de Convenciones.''] Por Jason Rodríguez Grafal. La Perla del Sur. Ponce, Puerto Rico. 12 October 2012. Retrieved 13 October 2012.</ref> and '''Complejo Ferial de Puerto Rico Juan H. Cintrón Garcia''', is a 3,000-seat<ref>[http://www.periodicolaperla.com/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=3348:primer-vistazo-a-su-interior-asi-luce-el-centro-de-convenciones-de-ponce&catid=81:locales&Itemid=198 ''Así luce el nuevo Centro de Convenciones.''] Jason Rodríguez Grafal. La Perla del Sur. Ponce, Puerto Rico. Year 30. Issue 1460. Page 4. 22 November 2011. Retrieved 28 April 2012.</ref> indoor [[arena]] and [[convention center]] in [[Ponce, Puerto Rico]]. It is intended to be used primarily for [[trade shows]], [[Convention (meeting)|conventions]] and [[sporting events]]. It opened in June, 2012.<ref>[http://www.periodicolaperla.com/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=3348:primer-vistazo-a-su-interior-asi-luce-el-centro-de-convenciones-de-ponce&catid=81:locales&Itemid=198 ''Así luce el nuevo Centro de Convenciones.''] Jason Rodríguez Grafal. La Perla del Sur. Ponce, Puerto Rico. Vol 30. Issue 1460. Page 4. 22 November 2011. Retrieved 28 April 2012.</ref> One of the first pre-inauguration activities was a set of [[Olympic Games|Olympic]] [[boxing]] pre-match games.<ref>[http://www.periodicolaperla.com/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=4003:adelantan-el-boxeo-de-la-copa-olimpica&catid=92:portada-deportes&Itemid=318 ''Adelantan el boxeo de la Copa Olímpica.''] Reinaldo Millán. La Perla del Sur. Ponce, Puerto Rico. Year 30. Number 1488. Page 60. 6 June 2012. Retrieved 6 June 2012.</ref><ref>[http://www.noticel.com/noticia/125280/otro-olimpico-a-la-final-en-ponce.html ''Otro olímpico a la final en Ponce.''] 7 June 2012. Noticel. Retrieved 28 June 2012.</ref> Its official inauguration was subsequently set for September 2012.<ref>[http://www.periodicolaperla.com/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=4046:durante-julio-pasara-a-corporacion-municipal-el-nuevo-centro-de-convenciones-de-ponce&catid=81:locales&Itemid=198 ''Primer paso con Centro de Convenciones.''] Jason Rodríguez Grafal. La Perla del Sur. Ponce, Puerto Rico. 20 June 2012. Year 30. Issue 1490. Page 10. Retrieved 20 June 2012.</ref> However, its official inauguration took place on 11 October 2012.<ref>[http://www.periodicolaperla.com/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=4363:sigue-sin-operador-el-centro-de-convenciones&catid=135:actualidad-del-sur&Itemid=423 ''Sin operador el Centro de Convenciones.''] Por Jason Rodríguez Grafal. La Perla del Sur. Ponce, Puerto Rico. 12 October 2012. Retrieved 13 October 2012.</ref>
The center was built to serve the local as well as the international business market.<ref>[http://www.periodicolaperla.com/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=3348:primer-vistazo-a-su-interior-asi-luce-el-centro-de-convenciones-de-ponce&catid=81:locales&Itemid=198 ''Así luce el nuevo Centro de Convenciones.''] Jason Rodríguez Grafal. La Perla del Sur. Ponce, Puerto Rico. Vol 30. Issue 1460. Page 4. 22 November 2011. Retrieved 28 April 2012.</ref> The Centro de Convenciones de Ponce was named after former Ponce Mayor [[Juan H. Cintrón García]].<ref>[http://www.primerahora.com/centrodeconvencionesdeponcellevaranombredeexalcaldejuancintron-471046.html ''Centro de Convenciones de Ponce llevará nombre de ex alcalde Juan Cintrón.''] Primera Hora. San Juan, Puerto Rico. 4 February 2011. Retrieved 28 April 2012.</ref><ref>[http://www.elsuralavista.com/periodico/?p=33612 ''Ya tiene nombre el Centro de Convenciones de Ponce.''] El Sur a la Vista. Ponce, Puerto Rico. 4 February 2011. Retrieved 28 April 2012.</ref> Centro de Convenciones de Ponce is unique among other [[convention center]]s in [[Puerto Rico]] for the flexibility of its interior spaces.<ref>[http://www.planosycapacetes.com/PDF/PyC14.pdf ''A todo vapor: Construcción Centro de Convenciones de Ponce.''] Planos y Capacetes. May–June 2009. Page 8. Retrieved 28 April 2012.</ref> It is owned by the Autonomous Municipality of Ponce.<ref>[http://www.planosycapacetes.com/PDF/PyC14.pdf ''A todo vapor: Construcción Centro de Convenciones de Ponce.''] Planos y Capacetes. May–June 2009. Page 8. Retrieved 28 April 2012.</ref>
==History== Construction of the structure started on 20 October 2008,<ref>[https://www.adendi.com/archivo.asp?Xnum=473106&year=2008&mon=10 ''Construirán centro de negocios en Ponce.''] Yaritza Santiago Caraballo. El Nuevo Dia. Guaynabo, Puerto Rico. 14 October 2008. Retrieved 28 April 2012.</ref><ref>[http://www.periodicolaperla.com/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=3348:primer-vistazo-a-su-interior-asi-luce-el-centro-de-convenciones-de-ponce&catid=81:locales&Itemid=198 ''Así luce el nuevo Centro de Convenciones.''] Jason Rodríguez Grafal. La Perla del Sur. Ponce, Puerto Rico. Vol 30. Issue 1460. Page 4. 22 November 2011. Retrieved 28 April 2012.</ref> under the administration of Mayor [[Francisco Zayas Seijo]].<ref> [http://www.periodicolaperla.com/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=569:soplan-vientos-de-cambio-para-el-centro-de-convenciones&catid=81:locales&Itemid=198 ''En la mesa de la Alcaldesa de Ponce: ¿Cambios para el Centro de Convenciones?''] Jason Rodríguez Grafal. La Perla del Sur. Ponce, Puerto Rico. Retrieved 28 April 2012.</ref> The building design was commissioned to architect Fernando Gonzalez Diaz and his architectural firm Urban Venture Group.{{citation needed|date=January 2017}} Urban Venture Group with their consultants; Pedro Dario Del Nero (structural engineer), Jorge Ledón Webster (mechanical engineer), Ricardo Rodriguez Del Valle (electrical engineer), Alfred J. Longhitano (codes) and Manuel Quilichini (civil engineer), formed the team that developed the Architecture and Interior design of "Complejo Ferial de Puerto Rico".{{citation needed|date=January 2017}} The structure was built by local Ponce construction company Venegas Construction.<ref>[http://www.periodicolaperla.com/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=3348:primer-vistazo-a-su-interior-asi-luce-el-centro-de-convenciones-de-ponce&catid=81:locales&Itemid=198 ''Así luce el nuevo Centro de Convenciones.''] Jason Rodríguez Grafal. La Perla del Sur. Ponce, Puerto Rico. Vol 30. Issue 1460. Page 4. 22 November 2011. Retrieved 28 April 2012.</ref> It was ordered by the Autonomous Municipality of Ponce at a cost of $41 million [[USD]], excluding its access roads and parking lot. These engaged an additional $3.9 million.<ref>[http://www.periodicolaperla.com/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=4046:durante-julio-pasara-a-corporacion-municipal-el-nuevo-centro-de-convenciones-de-ponce&catid=81:locales&Itemid=198 ''Primer paso con Centro de Convenciones.''] Jason Rodríguez Grafal. La Perla del Sur. Ponce, Puerto Rico. 20 June 2012. Year 30. Issue 1490. Page 10. Retrieved 20 June 2012.</ref><ref>[http://www.periodicolaperla.com/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=3348:primer-vistazo-a-su-interior-asi-luce-el-centro-de-convenciones-de-ponce&catid=81:locales&Itemid=198 ''Así luce el nuevo Centro de Convenciones.''] Jason Rodríguez Grafal. La Perla del Sur. Ponce, Puerto Rico. Vol 30. Issue 1460. Page 4. 22 November 2011. Retrieved 28 April 2012.</ref> Some 400 workmen labored in the construction of the structure.<ref>[http://www.planosycapacetes.com/PDF/PyC14.pdf ''A todo vapor: Construcción Centro de Convenciones de Ponce.''] Planos y Capacetes. May–June 2009. Page 8. Retrieved 28 April 2012.</ref>
==Management== The Center is managed by a public municipal corporation independent of the Municipal Government but which reports to it.<ref>[http://www.periodicolaperla.com/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=4046:durante-julio-pasara-a-corporacion-municipal-el-nuevo-centro-de-convenciones-de-ponce&catid=81:locales&Itemid=198 ''Primer paso con Centro de Convenciones.''] Jason Rodríguez Grafal. La Perla del Sur. Ponce, Puerto Rico. 20 June 2012. Year 30. Issue 1490. Page 10. Retrieved 20 June 2012.</ref> The corporation is headed by a five-member governing board. According to current by-laws of the municipality, one of the members of the governing body must be the municipal finance director, and the other four members are appointed by the mayor. The primary objective in creating a municipal corporation for the management and administration of Centro de Convenciones is "to exempt it from being bound by the bureocracy required by the Law of Autonomous Municipalities"<ref>[http://www.periodicolaperla.com/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=4046:durante-julio-pasara-a-corporacion-municipal-el-nuevo-centro-de-convenciones-de-ponce&catid=81:locales&Itemid=198 ''Primer paso con Centro de Convenciones.''] Jason Rodríguez Grafal. La Perla del Sur. Ponce, Puerto Rico. 20 June 2012. Year 30. Issue 1490. Page 10. Retrieved 20 June 2012.</ref> One of the obligations of the new corporation is to sign a long-term contract with an operator for the administration and day-to-day operation of the Center.<ref>[http://www.periodicolaperla.com/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=4046:durante-julio-pasara-a-corporacion-municipal-el-nuevo-centro-de-convenciones-de-ponce&catid=81:locales&Itemid=198 ''Primer paso con Centro de Convenciones.''] Jason Rodríguez Grafal. La Perla del Sur. Ponce, Puerto Rico. 20 June 2012. Year 30. Issue 1490. Page 10. Retrieved 20 June 2012.</ref> Various companies were mentioned as potential managers and interested parties, including [[SMG (property management)|SMG Worldwide Entertainment and Convention Venue Management]], Intertrade Development Group, and [[Destilería Serrallés|Grupo Serralles]], owners of the Ponce Hilton Resort and Casino.<ref>[http://www.periodicolaperla.com/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=4363:sigue-sin-operador-el-centro-de-convenciones&catid=135:actualidad-del-sur&Itemid=423 ''Sin operador el Centro de Convenciones.''] Por Jason Rodríguez Grafal. La Perla del Sur. Ponce, Puerto Rico. 12 October 2012. Retrieved 13 October 2012.</ref> In the end, Intertrade Development Group was chosen as the operator.<ref>[http://www.periodicolaperla.com/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=4418:a-manos-poncenas-la-operacion-del-centro-de-convenciones&catid=81:locales&Itemid=198 ''Ganan llave del Centro de Convenciones.''] Omar Alfonso. La Perla del Sur. Ponce, Puerto Rico. Year 30. Issue 1509. Page 4. (Title in printed edition: ''A manos ponceñas la operación del Centro de Convenciones.'') 31 October 2012. Retrieved 1 November 2012.</ref>
==Features== The building is a two-story structure.<ref>[http://www.elsuralavista.com/periodico/?p=27366 ''Centro de Convenciones de Ponce podrá operar.''] El Sur a la Vista. Ponce, Puerto Rico. Retrieved 28 April 2012.</ref> The main exhibit hall features 120,000 square feet of exhibit space.<ref>[http://www.periodicolaperla.com/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=3348:primer-vistazo-a-su-interior-asi-luce-el-centro-de-convenciones-de-ponce&catid=81:locales&Itemid=198 ''Así luce el nuevo Centro de Convenciones.''] Jason Rodríguez Grafal. La Perla del Sur. Ponce, Puerto Rico. Vol 30. Issue 1460. Page 4. 22 November 2011. Retrieved 28 April 2012.</ref> The main exhibit hall can be structured into 16 smaller and independent mixed-used rooms to simultaneously accommodate various activities, such as conventions, concerts, weddings, and corporate meetings.<ref>[http://www.periodicolaperla.com/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=3348:primer-vistazo-a-su-interior-asi-luce-el-centro-de-convenciones-de-ponce&catid=81:locales&Itemid=198 ''Así luce el nuevo Centro de Convenciones.''] Jason Rodríguez Grafal. La Perla del Sur. Ponce, Puerto Rico. Vol 30. Issue 1460. Page 4. 22 November 2011. Retrieved 28 April 2012.</ref> Each of the 16 rooms will have its own independently controlled climate and sound systems.<ref>[http://www.periodicolaperla.com/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=3348:primer-vistazo-a-su-interior-asi-luce-el-centro-de-convenciones-de-ponce&catid=81:locales&Itemid=198 ''Así luce el nuevo Centro de Convenciones.''] Jason Rodríguez Grafal. La Perla del Sur. Ponce, Puerto Rico. Vol 30. Issue 1460. Page 4. 22 November 2011. Retrieved 28 April 2012.</ref> The property also features a planned parking lot with capacity for 700 vehicles.<ref>[http://www.elsuralavista.com/periodico/?p=27366 ''Centro de Convenciones de Ponce podrá operar.''] El Sur a la Vista. Ponce, Puerto Rico. Retrieved 28 April 2012.</ref> There is also an area with a view of [[Rio Portugues]] with a capacity for 300 persons.<ref>[http://www.planosycapacetes.com/PDF/PyC14.pdf ''A todo vapor: Construcción Centro de Convenciones de Ponce.''] Planos y Capacetes. May–June 2009. Page 8. Retrieved 28 April 2012.</ref> The Puerto Rico Senate voted to name this structure "Centro de Convenciones de Ponce [[Juan H. Cintron]]" in honor to the Ponce politician.<ref>[http://www.primerahora.com/centrodeconvencionesdeponcellevaranombredeexalcaldejuancintron-471046.html ''Centro de Convenciones de Ponce llevará nombre de ex alcalde Juan Cintrón.''] Primera Hora. 4 February 2011. Retrieved 28 September 2012.</ref>
==Notable events== An international design festival, Boom Fair 2013, took place during August 2013.<ref>[http://www.periodicolaperla.com/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=5351:se-congregaran-en-ponce-disenadores-de-latinoamerica&catid=81:locales&Itemid=198 ''Celebrarán en Ponce feria de diseñadores.''] Reinaldo Millán. La Perla del Sur. Ponce, Puerto Rico. Year 31. Issue 1550. Page 12. 14 August 2013. Retrieved 14 August 2013.</ref> A cardiovascular health symposium, sponsored by [[Hospital Episcopal San Lucas]], followed on 24 August 2013.<ref>[http://www.periodicolaperla.com/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=5368:magno-evento-de-salud-en-el-centro-de-convenciones&catid=119:articulos&Itemid=342 ''Magno evento en Centro de Convenciones.''] La Perla del Sur. Ponce, Puerto Rico. Year 31. Issue 1551. Page 26. 21 August 2013. Retrieved 21 August 2013.</ref>
