[[File:HSS klubblokal.jpg|thumb|240px|Helsingfors Segelsällskap Clubhouse]] 
'''Liuskasaari''' ({{lang-sv|Skifferholmen}}) is an island located south of [[Helsinki]], [[Finland]]. This island is home of the [[Helsingfors Segelsällskap]], one of the oldest sailing clubs in Finland. The island hosts two restaurants: The HSS Clubhouse Restaurant and the Skiffer outdoor restaurant. This island has about 50 000 visitors annually and can be reached by a ferry that traffics the island from the [[Meripuisto|Merisatama park]].

The island hosted some of the [[Sailing at the 1952 Summer Olympics|sailing]] events for the [[1952 Summer Olympics]].

==References==
* [https://web.archive.org/web/20080411091045/http://www.la84foundation.org/6oic/OfficialReports/1952/OR1952.pdf 1952 Summer Olympics official report.] p.&nbsp;58.
